<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/7326> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #7326" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Prefect. Placed in command (#) by M. Lucullus, imperator, of the city of Mesembria on the Pontic coast of Thrace, he was honored by the city as benefactor and patron (Detchev, Bull. Arch. Inst. Sophia 17, 1950, 59-64, known to me from J. and L. Robert, Bull. epig. 1952, p. 156 f. and 1954, no. 177; G. Tibiletti, Governatori romani in citta provinciali, RIL 86, 1953, 64-100, esp. 70f.).\n" .
